# Validation & Errors

## Joi middleware

```js
export const XValidation = ErrorCatch(async (req, res, next) => {
  const schema = joi.object({ /* fields */ });
  const { error } = schema.validate(req.body, { abortEarly: false });
  if (error) {
    const errorMessages = error.details.map((e) => e.message).join(". ");
    return res.status(400).json({ error: errorMessages });
  }
  next();
});
```

## Global errors

- Controllers: wrap with `ErrorCatch` from `src/utils/ErrorCatch.js`
- Router 404 / global handler in `app.router.js` uses `error.cause` as status
- Prefer `success: false` + `message` for app errors; validation uses `{ error: "..." }`

## Rules

- Add custom `.messages({...})` on Joi fields (match auth validation style)
- Validate `req.body` with `abortEarly: false` when collecting multiple field errors
- Call `next()` only after validation passes
